Friday Olokor, Abuja The Independent National Electoral Commission has released additional 40 vehicles to the Presidential Task Force on COVID-19 to complement its efforts in the fight against coronavirus. INEC National Commissioner and chairman of its Information and Voter Education Committee, Festus Okoye, said this in a statement on Wednesday. He said, “In response to the request by the Presidential Task Force on combating on COVID-19 for more vehicles to support the national emergency against coronavirus emergency, the commission has deployed about 40 additional vehicles. “Thirty pick-up vans have been deployed in Kano to facilitate the movement of medical personnel while nine vehicles have been assigned to Plateau State.” Okoye had told The PUNCH that INEC would continue assisting the Presidential Task Force on COVID-19 in areas where it had comparative advantage. The commission specifically said it was willing and able to release additional vehicles and drivers to the PTF if they so requested. The commission had recently donated 100 pick-up vans to assist the government in the fight against COVID-19. Copyright PUNCH.
